entries.femaleVariant: River?!
We can breach the fence, then look for a way inside.

Knowing their funding, I wouldn't expect much pushback from security.
Likely the room where they edit the autistic kids' dreams.
Yawen!
Harris' s dream BD – where is it?
A bullet damaged his cerebral cortex. We get only dissonant urges, pieces.
Barely know each other.
Hasn't let me down yet.
Barely know River. We just work together.
River and I get along, we're friends. Hasn't let me down yet.
Do not believe any promise he makes!
Good tip, thanks, but we're wastin' time.
That why you're refusin' to help 'im out?
entries.maleVariant: Is that why you're refusin' to help 'im out?

entries.femaleVariant: What? Why?!
But he isn't on the spectrum.
A favorite song or movie helps you reach the kids – might be worth a try.
Dead end, River. I'm sorry.
Looks like a dead end, River. I’m sorry.
Audio-visual stimulation – that's what we gotta try.
I'd like to--
Try audio-visual stimulation.
It's an experimental procedure, but it's already yielding results.
And we're now headed to…?
Empty braindance case.
It's a braindance editing terminal. You familiar?
V! I think it's this room!
C'mere, help me search it!
On my way!
They record dreams that can be played back as BDs.
A little.
Hey, River! Think I got it!
Hey, V.
So what's the issue?
So, what happened?
Nice ride. Brand new?
Wouldn't let it go if I were you.
No way I'd let this lie.
And what, they figured you'd get emotional and kept you off the case?
They're not all wrong – got a personal stake in this.
entries.maleVariant: They're not all wrong – ya got a personal stake in this.

entries.femaleVariant: Randy's disappearance – know anything else?
entries.maleVariant: Randy's disappearance – you know anything else?

entries.femaleVariant: Nice ride.
They're not completely wrong.
I know. And that's why I'm askin' for your help.
More like a restraining order – won't let me anywhere near it.
How ya holdin' up?
Been better.
Nope.
Not in a chatty mood, I see.
Not really. Sorry.
What's the problem if they caught the guy?
My nephew, Randy... Disappeared not long past.
And what you just saw – the kid was wearin' Randy's shoes.
Oh Jesus…
Gonaghal took the lead on it – a lazy-ass gonk. And so far he ain't accomplished shit.
And that's why I need an objective eye – you.
My sister and I don't get along that well… I don't know much.
Just wish I coulda been there for her when she needed it most.
What are you doing here?! You got kicked off the force!
Who are you?
What'd she mean by that?
And who might you be?
I'm calling the actual police!
W-wait, wait, wait, hear… hear me out, please.
He hasn't told you?
Yawen, please listen to me…
Aren't you in enough trouble already?!
Harris kidnapped my nephew.
Remember your first med school exam?
You know the one. Passed it with flying colors.
Can't leave without Peter Pan's scrolls.
NCPD won't solve this.
Can't leave without Peter Pan's dreams.
entries.maleVariant: We can't leave without Peter Pan's dreams.

entries.femaleVariant: Listen, you work with badges, right? You know what they're like.
I'll say it one last time – OUT.
This type of thinking is the very reason we live in a lawless city.
I cannot believe you would throw that in my face!
Hah! I thought us friends, too!
Let's try it.
We don't even know his preferences!
I'll find somethin'. That mean you're willin' to try?
Just... go. I'll open the front door for you.
I am aware of the similarity – hypothalamus stimulation and hormone production.
Comin'!
Haven't been assigned to the search?
The disappearance – tell me more.
Know where they're keepin' the BD?
[Open cabinet] Was breaking in necessary?
This man – he only takes! He never gives anything back!
entries.maleVariant: You don't know him well, do you? This man is a bastard!

entries.femaleVariant: I know, prolly not hard to tell.
So whadda we need to do?
Can't interrogate the guy 'cause he's a veg, but… we can view his dreams.
Sorry… dreams?
You heard me. C'mon, I'll explain on the way.
Seriously, River? You weren't in enough trouble already?
"Lawless"?
Dammit, Yawen! Who the fuck do you think you are?
Gotta remember it. Ladies' room erupted in flame, they evacuated everybody for two hours…
I never wish to see you here again!
Any reason you haven't?
Try now.
Any specific reason why?
Because, unlike River, I went to med school and studied neuroscience.
A lab. To get the BDs of Peter Pan's dreams.
OK, got an appointment?
Not exactly. We'll go in together, but uh…
Should be labeled as Anthony Harris.
Just suspended, actually.
I'm sorry, really I am, but we store evidence here, and we have strict protocols.
Talkin' about saving a child's life, here.
"Protocols"? Talkin' about his nephew's life, here!
Randy and the other boys… they're out there somewhere. Waitin' for help.
A child's life!
This is an ongoing police investigation.
I need to do whatever I can to find them.
River, the police are investigating.
Go, please.
Get out now!
Not through the main entrance.
We'll find a different way in and then hustle out quick.
Oh, we're gonna break the law?!
entries.maleVariant: Ah, we're gonna break the law?!

entries.femaleVariant: Never actually been here, so I'll need your help.
Great. What now?
How we gonna find this braindance?
Look for a room where they edit the dreams of autistic kids.
Oh, and remember – Peter Pan's real name is Anthony Harris.
OK. Shouldn't be anyone inside. The lab's in the middle of an audit. So make all the noise you want.
They have an audit today – should be a ghost town. No need to be quiet.
Nothin' here. No sign of any BDs.
Right, nothin'.
Hmph. Locked, can't get in.
Got some kinda shard, but it's blank. Keep lookin'.
Found something?
Not yet.
Anthony Harris.
Let's try these drawers.
Anthony Harris.
Kids with autism, you said?
Someone wants to be a cop when they grow up.
Tech's half-decent.
Bill Graham?
All set to record…
Needed someone to talk to.
First, take a look.
Mhm?
More municipal politics?
More dead politicians?
Just watch it.
Yeah, they got a research grant.
Hm, they got budget-savvy management.
Uh, no, Anthony Harris.
Sure know a lot…
Feed 'em analysis, they'll shit out failure.
Especially you!
But Harris is not a child. I have never tried the procedure on an adult.
And not by reading about it over someone's shoulder on the metro.
V! Not that way!
Headed back to the lab. I'll wait for ya there.
I'm here.
OK, where were we?
Be back later.
Be back later.
Let's move.
Hurry back, please. Randy's out there somewhere, needs our help.
Well, this is the place... Tick tick tick…
A few of these rooms we probably don't have to bother with.
They definitely don't store any BDs in this area.
Where we goin'?
Got access to these dreams?
Got access to these dreams?
entries.maleVariant: Ya got access to these dreams?

entries.femaleVariant: Not yet, but they keep them in the lab we're headed to now.
So? Looks like they caught him.
This Peter Pan a case of yours?
This "Peter Pan" – he an old case, you were lookin' for 'im?
entries.maleVariant: This, uh, "Peter Pan" – he an old case, you were lookin' for 'im?

entries.femaleVariant: Never heard of him. Didn't cross my desk.
Let's ride, V.
I know exactly where to start.
We find our entrance.
He isn't dreaming.
Say, River? Why not just have a janitor crack a door for ya?
Can't risk gettin' scolded for sniffin' around somebody else's case.
Cops seem to like you. Could be this one's sniffin' around for somethin' extra?
entries.maleVariant: Cops seem to like you. Careful this one doesn't start sendin' you out for donuts.

entries.femaleVariant: River's all right.
Not your biz, Johnny.
Stay out of it, Johnny.
Oooh... Think someone actually wants to polish Mr. Policeman's badge.
entries.maleVariant: Wait, meanin' you're willin' to traipse along behind Mr. Policeman like a pup?

entries.femaleVariant: Y'know, moments like these I truly mourn the fact I can't fuckin' sock you one.
Fine, not gonna pry. Truth is you coulda done worse than Detective "Blue Moon" Ward.
Already have. Got a brain parasite nibblin' away at my nerve endings as we speak.
Whaa? No, River's all right.
Mh, yeeeah.
Can tell ya got somethin' to say, so say it.
entries.maleVariant: Not every cop's a bastard, just like not every rockerboy's a narcissistic dickhead.

entries.femaleVariant: Me? No, no. Just maybe this cop's flyin' straight in your pants.

Just trash.
Just some trash...
Mini-cop…
Kids with autism?
Not bad as tech goes.
HR documents... better keep looking.

I did my homework.

I wanna see for myself.

[Get in]
[Get out]

Shut your mouth!
